# Rational Function and Asymptotes 

## Vertical Asymptotes

 $f(x)= \cfrac {q(x)}{p(x)} (polynomial function), q(x)\neq0)$

## Horizontal Asymptotes

${\lim_{x\to+\infin}}f(x)=a$ or ${\lim_{x\to-\infin}}f(x)=a$

## Oblique Asymptotes

${\lim_{x\to+\infin}\frac{f(x)}{x}}=A$

${\lim_{x\to+\infin}[f(x)-Ax]}=B$

$y=Ax+B$
